# ice-matlab credential fallback file
#
# COPY THIS FILE TO .env (same directory) AND FILL IN YOUR VALUES.
# .env is gitignored. .env.example is committed as documentation only.
#
# The preferred place to store credentials is the MATLAB Vault — run
# ice.config.setupVault() once and you can leave this file unused.
# Use a .env when:
#   - the Vault is unavailable (CI, container, headless dev machine)
#   - you need credentials portable to another user account on the same box
#
# Resolution order for ice.config.credentials("KEY"):
#   1. MATLAB Vault (getSecret)
#   2. .env file at toolbox root  (this file)
#   3. Process environment variable
#
# Format rules:
#   - One KEY=value per line.
#   - Lines starting with # are comments.
#   - Blank lines are ignored.
#   - Only the FIRST '=' splits key from value; values may contain '='.
#   - Surrounding double-quotes around a value are stripped:
#       PWD="  has spaces  " -> "  has spaces  "
#   - The key must be a valid MATLAB identifier (letters, digits, underscore,
#     starting with a letter); malformed lines are silently skipped.
#   - No shell expansion, no variable interpolation, no multi-line values.

# --- ICE FTP / SFTP credentials --------------------------------------------
ICE_FTP_USER=
ICE_FTP_PWD=

# --- ICE Connect Enterprise XML API credentials ----------------------------
# Fill in once UAT access is granted.
ICE_API_USER=
ICE_API_PWD=

# --- Optional overrides ----------------------------------------------------
# Override the default cache root (D:\matlab\data) for production deployments
# or to move the cache onto a network share. Same value can be set as a
# Windows environment variable instead.
# ICE_CACHE_ROOT=E:\ice-cache
